                  <p>---</p>


                  <p>If you want to meet a Dark Watcher, you should bring a gift.</p>


                  <p>Steinbeck’s mother Olive Hamilton brought fruit or sometimes flowers. Steinbeck’s son Thomas said his grandmother, a school teacher, was no fabulist, but she believed firmly in the Dark Watchers. She told her children and grandchildren she left fruit or nuts in Mule Deer Canyon on her way to school in Big Sur. On the way back, there would be flowers in their place.</p><div class="adModule adModule--outer "><div id="CONCERT2" class="adModule--inner loaded" data-slug="Advertisement" data-disclaimer="Article continues below this ad" data-small="300" data-google-query-id="CIOC_-ixpu8CFZXUUQodSZAF7A"><div id="google_ads_iframe_/36117602/hnp-sfgate.com/Local_3__container__" style="border: 0pt none; display: inline-block; width: 100%; height: auto;"><iframe frameborder="0" src="https://9c31b5aaba6a8617e576cbc48ec2f2a5.safeframe.googlesyndication.com/safeframe/1-0-37/html/container.html" id="google_ads_iframe_/36117602/hnp-sfgate.com/Local_3" title="3rd party ad content" name="" scrolling="no" marginwidth="0" marginheight="0" width="0" height="0" data-is-safeframe="true" sandbox="allow-forms allow-popups allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox allow-same-origin allow-scripts allow-top-navigation-by-user-activation" allow="conversion-measurement ‘src’" data-google-container-id="4" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: bottom; min-width: 100%;" data-load-complete="true"></iframe></div></div></div>


          <!-- Missed: ad -->

                  <p>The stories stuck with Steinbeck, clearly, and were echoed by Big Sur personalities like Doc Ricketts and <a href="https://www.latimes.com/local/obituaries/la-me-billy-post2-2009aug02-story.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Billy Post</a>.</p>


                  <p>"The old timers of Big Sur swear by it," painter Benjamin Brode, who <a href="http://www.darkwatchersbook.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">co-authored a book</a> on the watchers with Thomas Steinbeck, <a href="https://www.montereycountyweekly.com/people/831/big-sur-is-home-to-shadowy-figures-or-at-least-people-who-see-them/article_ab3725be-b9be-11e7-aa73-43df29d5070d.amp.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">told the Monterey County Weekly</a> in 2017.</p>

